# FileExporter

This Extension is inspired by the DataExporter widget for Thingworx 6.0. The time has passed since then and the extension needs some updates.
Right now it only supports PDF exporting, but depending on the future requests it will be enhanced!


## How to use?

There are changes to this Extension. In DataExporter there was a pre created Thing based on a custom file repository class.
This is deprecated in last Extension SDK releases.

Right now this extension will add a new ThingShape instead!

1. Create a new Thing. I recommend to use a File Repository
2. Add the **FileExporter** ThingShape to it
3. Execute one of the Service below 

Note: Till yet only flat Infotables are supported no nested ones 


### Services

ExportInfotableAsPdf

Input Parameter | Description 
---------|----------
 infotable | the Infotable you want to export
 fileName | the name of the generated PDF (if empty it will generated as "Export-YYYY-MM-DD_hh-mm-ss") 
 fileRepository | the File Repository Thing which where the exported file should be saved 


### Example Service

```
// CreateInfoTableFromDataShape(infoTableName:STRING("InfoTable"), dataShapeName:STRING):INFOTABLE(Test.DS)
let it = Resources["InfoTableFunctions"].CreateInfoTableFromDataShape({
    infoTableName: "InfoTable",
    dataShapeName: "Test.DS"
});

let tobj = new Object();
tobj.A = "AAAAA";
tobj.B = "BB"
tobj.Image = ""

it.AddRow(tobj);

// result: STRING
let result = me.ExportInfotableAsPdf({
	fileName: "FileName" /* STRING */,
	fileRepository: "FileRepo" /* THINGNAME [Required] */,
	infotable: it /* INFOTABLE [Required] */
});
```
